#: ../../../versioning.rst:5
msgid "Versioning and API Stability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:8
msgid "Versioning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:10
msgid "Scrapy uses the `odd-numbered versions for development releases`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:12
msgid "There are 3 numbers in a Scrapy version: *A.B.C*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:14
msgid ""
"*A* is the major version. This will rarely change and will signify very "
"large changes. So far, only zero is available for *A* as Scrapy hasn't yet "
"reached 1.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:17
msgid ""
"*B* is the release number. This will include many changes including features "
"and things that possibly break backwards compatibility. Even Bs will be "
"stable branches, and odd Bs will be development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:20
msgid "*C* is the bugfix release number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:22
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:24
msgid ""
"*0.14.1* is the first bugfix release of the *0.14* series (safe to use in "
"production)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:28
msgid "API Stability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:30
msgid ""
"API stability is one of Scrapy major goals for the *1.0* release, which "
"doesn't have a due date scheduled yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:33
msgid ""
"Methods or functions that start with a single dash (``_``) are private and "
"should never be relied as stable. Besides those, the plan is to stabilize "
"and document the entire API, as we approach the 1.0 release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:37
msgid ""
"Also, keep in mind that stable doesn't mean complete: stable APIs could grow "
"new methods or functionality but the existing methods should keep working "
"the same way."
msgstr ""
